These are Puzzles for 2x6 Level 2

.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-2-1::.
6 different games are played: chess, scrabble, bridge, whist, monopoly, mah-jongg
There 6 different types of food: kale, spinach, cranberry, peas, avocado, apricot
1. the person playing whist is on the left of the person playing bridge##1
2. the person eating spinach is on the left of the person playing mah-jongg##1
3. the person playing chess is on the left of the person playing scrabble##1
4. the person eating avocado is between the person playing mah-jongg and the person eating kale##2
5. the person eating peas is between the person eating avocado and the person eating spinach##2
6. the person eating kale is the person playing whist##1
7. the person playing monopoly is on the left of the person eating kale##1
8. the person eating apricot is on the left of the person playing scrabble##1
9. the person playing monopoly is on the right of the person playing mah-jongg##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1    |      2      |       3       |       4        |    5     |   6    |
| Game           | chess | scrabble | mah-jongg | monopoly | whist    | bridge  |
| Food   | apricot | spinach   | peas       | avocado        | kale | cranberry |

